  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>JennAir — Whirlpool luxury with 2020 design-language split</h2>
    <p>JennAir was founded in 1947 in Indianapolis and became known for the downdraft cooktop invented by Lou Jenn in the mid-1960s. Whirlpool acquired JennAir in 1981 and has positioned it as Whirlpool North America's luxury brand alongside Whirlpool (premium), Maytag (mass-market), and KitchenAid (premium with specific small-appliance emphasis). The 2020 brand relaunch refreshed JennAir's entire lineup — including the wall oven category — with a two-tier design-language split: Rise Collection (bold statement) and Nord Collection (quiet minimalist). The relaunch targeted luxury customers at both aesthetic preferences, positioning JennAir directly against Wolf + Thermador + Miele at the dedicated luxury wall-oven tier.</p>
    <p>For LA service economics, the Whirlpool-family parts infrastructure supports JennAir reliably: common service parts (bake elements, sensors, door hardware) run 2-4 day lead through JennAir's dedicated distribution combined with Whirlpool-family parts network where applicable. Specialty Rise + Nord generation-specific components (current-generation control boards, specific cosmetic trim variants) can run 3-7 days. We stock common JennAir service parts on the truck for single-visit resolution.</p>
  </div></section>

