  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Rise vs Nord — service implications</h2>
    <p>Rise and Nord share the same core wall oven mechanical platform — bake elements, convection systems, control architectures interchange at the component level between models of comparable spec and generation. The differences are aesthetic trim (handles, control panel design, finish materials, visual design language) rather than mechanical. For service, this means:</p>
    <p><b>Mechanical service is tier-agnostic</b> — a bake element on a Rise 30" single wall oven and a Nord 30" single wall oven of comparable generation is the same part. Convection fan motors, sensors, thermostats, door hinges, and many control-board variants interchange.</p>
    <p><b>Cosmetic trim is tier-specific</b> — Rise handle hardware, Rise control panel bezels, Nord matte-finish panels, Nord flat-panel bezels — these are tier-specific and carry separate part numbers + parts-supply lead times.</p>
    <p><b>Control platform firmware</b> — firmware revisions can differ between Rise and Nord sub-variants in specific model years; we verify firmware version at diagnostic before committing to control-board work.</p>
    <p><b>2020 relaunch cutover</b> — pre-2020 JennAir wall ovens ran a different design language and different trim parts catalog. Parts supply for pre-2020 JennAir still works through Whirlpool-family distribution but lead times run longer on some specialty pre-2020 components.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Smart Oven+ Wi-Fi + app integration service</h2>
    <p>Smart Oven+ is JennAir's Wi-Fi + SmartThinQ-compatible app integration. Common Smart Oven+ service scenarios:</p>
    <p><b>Wi-Fi connectivity drops after router firmware updates</b> — repair the network connection, re-establish pairing, verify cycle-monitoring works again. Usually a firmware-side fix, not hardware.</p>
    <p><b>App pairing lost after control-board firmware update</b> — re-pair the appliance in the JennAir app, verify command responsiveness. Factory reset may be required if pairing state gets corrupted.</p>
    <p><b>Cook programs fail to execute from the app</b> — firmware check + factory reset resolves most; if hardware fault is downstream, the underlying mechanical issue is the real problem and smart-feature symptom is the tell.</p>
    <p><b>Smart-feature-specific sensors</b> — Steam+Convection humidity sensor, some Rise/Nord models have specific Smart Oven+ telemetry sensors. Sensor service $320-$540.</p>
    <p>Smart Oven+ fault diagnosis usually resolves at the firmware + connectivity level rather than requiring hardware replacement. Our approach on smart-feature service calls: verify the network + app + firmware layer first; escalate to hardware only when those are confirmed healthy.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Common JennAir wall oven faults</h2>
    <p><b>Rise or Nord bake element failure</b> — element lasts 8-12 years typical in LA residential use. Replacement $380-$620.</p>
    <p><b>Convection fan motor wear</b> — bearings develop play over years. Replacement $440-$720.</p>
    <p><b>Control board firmware lockout</b> — factory reset + firmware update resolves some; replacement $520-$880 when not.</p>
    <p><b>Temperature sensor drift</b> — cavity off-setpoint. Replacement $260-$420.</p>
    <p><b>Smart Oven+ connectivity issues</b> — usually firmware/network; $180-$320 service.</p>
    <p><b>Humidity sensor (Steam+Convection models)</b> — dedicated sensor for combi cycles. Replacement $320-$540.</p>
    <p><b>Steam+Convection water reservoir service</b> — reservoir, water valve, combi-cycle logic. Service $280-$460.</p>
    <p><b>Self-clean door-lock motor</b> — lock engagement failure. Replacement $280-$460.</p>
    <p><b>Door hinge wear</b> — develops play over years. Replacement $300-$500.</p>
    <p><b>Double wall oven per-cavity service</b> — upper or lower only. $420-$760.</p>
  </div></section>

